      "line": 421,
      "message": "It's not an error printing the trace, but closing the writer. Can be ignored because there's nothing that can be done about it, let alone that close() has no effect in StringWriter (https://docs.oracle.com/javase/7/docs/api/java/io/StringWriter.html#close()). Frankly, I don't know why StringWriter is used here. Please replace it with StringBuilder and make sure there is a unit tests in place. (StringWriter would be used with an API that accepts a java.io.Writer, which is not the case here).",
